r challenges for the core-periphery distinction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aConversation analysis. 0aMinimalist theory (Linguistics) 0aMinimalist theory (Linguistics). 0aStructural linguistics. 4aGrammatiktheorie. 4aKern und Peripherie. 4aSprachtheorie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aGrammar theory.  acore and periphery.  alanguage theory.1 aBohnemeyer, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButler, Lindsay K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinkbeiner, Rita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoschler, Juliana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJaeger, T. Florian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJiménez, Tomás, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrifka, Manfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMachicao y Priemer, Antonio, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMachicao, Antonio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeibauer, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Hans–Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNolda, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNolda, Andreas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOlsen, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPiñango, Maria M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPriemer, Antonio Machicao y, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabu